主要翻译
 
on adj (running, not switched off)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 开着, 打开的  
 -- The computer's already on.
 -- Keep your phone on in case I need to call you.
 -- 电脑已经开着了。// 电话不要关，等我给你打来。
 
!! on prep (atop)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 在…上 zài … shàng  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 在…上头 zài … shàng ，zài … shàng tou 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 在…上面 zài … shàng ，zài shàng miàn 
 -- Your book's on the table.
 -- 你的书在桌子上。
 
on prep (on the surface)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 在…上 zài … shàng  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 挂在…上 zài … shàng ，guà zài … shàng 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 以…为支撑 zài … shàng ，yǐ … wéi zhī chēng 
 -- The picture's on the wall.
 -- 画在墙上。
 
on prep (in the vicinity)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 靠近 kào jìn TC Traditional Chinese 靠近  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 在…旁 kào jìn，zài … páng 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 在…旁 kào jìn，zài … páng 
 -- They bought a house on a lake.
 -- 他们在湖边买了一栋房子。
 
on prep (part of)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 加入 jiā rù TC Traditional Chinese 加入  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 进入 jiā rù，jìn rù TC Traditional Chinese 進入 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 成为、…中的一员 
 -- He's been on the football team for several years.
 -- 他进球队几年了。
 
on prep (according to)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 根据 gēn jù TC Traditional Chinese 根據  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 凭借 gēn jù ，píng jiè TC Traditional Chinese 憑藉 
 -- We'll continue on that basis.
 -- 我们将在那个基础上继续。
 
on prep (purpose)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 为了 wèi le TC Traditional Chinese 為了  
 -- He's here on business.
 -- 他来办公事。
 
on prep (means)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 以…方式 yǐ … fāng shì  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 通过 yǐ … fāng shì，tōng guò TC Traditional Chinese 通過 
 -- His car runs on diesel.  Did you come here on foot?
 -- 他的车是柴油车。
 -- 你是走来的吗？
 
on adv (into position)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese …上  (放上)
 -- Put the lid on and boil for five minutes.
 -- 把盖子盖上，煮五分钟。
 
on prep (condition)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese [表示状况] [ biǎo shì zhuàng kuàng ]  
 -- The house is on fire.
 -- 房子着火了。
 
on prep (time, occasion)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 在...时候 TC Traditional Chinese 在…時候  (指时间)
 -- I always go jogging on Sundays.
 -- Let's go to the cinema on Tuesday.
 -- Are you available on 6 June?
 -- On that fateful day, Audrey had no idea what was about to happen to her.
 -- 我总是在周日去慢跑。//我们周二去看电影吧。//你6月6日有空吗？//在那命中注定的日子，奥黛丽不知道自己将要发生什么。
 
on adv (being worn)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 穿着 chuān zhe TC Traditional Chinese 穿著 / 穿着  
 -- The old lady was sitting on the bus with her hat and coat on.
 -- 穿大衣戴帽子那位老妇人坐在公交车上。

